<!-- Definition and symptoms -->
'''听力减退'''<ref>https://www.termonline.cn/word/145938/1#</ref>（hearing loss）又稱'''聽力缺損'''、'''聽力損失'''，簡稱'''失聽'''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://terms.naer.edu.tw/detail/717172/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2022-04-03 |archive-date=2022-04-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220403015614/https://terms.naer.edu.tw/detail/717172/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，屬於一種聽覺障礙，意思是[[聽力|聽力]]“減損”或“退化”，使致[[聽覺|聽覺]]部分或完全喪失<ref name="Britannica">{{cite encyclopedia|year=2011|title=Deafness|encyclopedia=Encyclopædia Britannica Online|publisher=Encyclopædia Britannica Inc.|location=|id=|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/154327/deafness|accessdate=2012-02-22|archive-date=2012-06-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120625153552/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/154327/deafness|dead-url=no}}</ref>；'''耳聾'''（deafness）又稱'''失聰'''，則是指完全沒有或幾乎沒有聽力<ref name="WHO2015">{{cite web|url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs300/en/|title=Deafness and hearing loss Fact sheet N°300|accessdate=23 May 2015|date=March 2015|archive-date=2015-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150516054114/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs300/en/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。聽力減退可能發生在單耳或雙耳，有可能是暫時或永久性質。孩童的聽力問題可能影響[[語言|語言]]學習，而對成人可能造成工作上的困難<ref name="Las2014">{{cite journal|title=Hearing loss: diagnosis and management.|last=Lasak|first=JM|date=Mar 2014|journal=Primary care|issue=1|doi=10.1016/j.pop.2013.10.003|volume=41|pages=19–31|pmid=24439878|author3=McVay, T|author4=Lewis, D|author2=Allen, P}}</ref>。對某些人而言，聽力減退可能造成孤獨感，尤其是老年人口。

<!-- Cause and diagnosis -->
聽力減退的可能成因包括：[[遺傳學|遺傳學]]、[[老化|老化]]、{{le|噪音引發的聽力減退|Noise-induced hearing loss|暴露於噪音環境}}、[[感染|感染]]、生產相關併發症、耳朵外傷、某些藥物或毒素。[[中耳炎|中耳炎]]是造成聽力減退的常見症狀，而妊娠期間的某些感染如[[梅毒|梅毒]]和[[風疹|風疹]]也可能造成聽力減退。建議所有新生兒都應接受聽覺測試<ref name="Las2014" />，若在測試中發現單耳或雙耳無法聽見25[[分貝|分貝]]的音量，則診斷為聽力減退<ref name=WHO2015/>。聽力減退可分級為輕度、中度、中度至重度、重度、深度，並主要分類為{{le|傳導性聽力喪失|Conductive hearing loss}}、[[感覺神經性耳聾|感覺神經性耳聾]]、混合性聽力喪失<ref name="Sm2014">{{cite journal|title=Deafness and Hereditary Hearing Loss Overview|first1=RJH|last2=Shearer|first2=AE|date=2014|pmid=20301607|last3=Hildebrand|first3=MS|last4=Van Camp|first4=G|last5=Pagon|first5=RA|last6=Adam|first6=MP|last7=Ardinger|first7=HH|last8=Wallace|first8=SE|last9=Amemiya|first9=A|last1=Smith|last10=Bean|first10=LJH|last11=Bird|first11=TD|last12=Fong|first12=CT|last13=Mefford|first13=HC|last14=Smith|first14=RJH|last15=Stephens|first15=K}}</ref>。

<!-- Prevention and treatment -->
半數聽力減退病例是可預防的，包含[[疫苗注射|疫苗注射]]、[[妊娠|妊娠]]照護、噪音防護，以及避免某些藥物。[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]建議年輕人使用[[可攜式媒體播放器|可攜式媒體播放器]]一日不要超過一小時<ref name="WHO2015Aud">{{cite web|url=http://www.who.int/pbd/deafness/activities/IECD_2015_Press_Release_EN.pdf?ua=1|title=1.1 billion people at risk of hearing loss WHO highlights serious threat posed by exposure to recreational noise|accessdate=2 March 2015|date=27 February 2015|website=who.int|archive-date=2015-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150501204444/http://www.who.int/pbd/deafness/activities/IECD_2015_Press_Release_EN.pdf?ua=1|dead-url=no}}</ref>。早期發現及支持治療對孩童尤其重要。[[助聽器|助聽器]]、[[手語|手語]]、[[人工耳蝸|人工耳蝸]]，及[[字幕|字幕]]對大多數患者有幫助。[[讀唇法|讀唇法]]也可以幫助患者的溝通。然而，世界上仍有許多地區無法對於聽力減退者給予適當的協助<ref name="WHO2015" />。

<!-- Epidemiology and culture-->
根據統計，2013年約十億人罹患不同程度的聽力減退<ref>{{cite journal|title=Global, regional, and national incidence, prevalence, and years lived with disability for 301 acute and chronic diseases and injuries in 188 countries, 1990-2013: a systematic analysis for the Global Burden of Disease Study 2013.|first1=Collaborators|date=22 August 2015|journal=Lancet (London, England)|issue=9995|doi=10.1016/s0140-6736(15)60692-4|volume=386|pages=743–800|pmc=4561509|pmid=26063472|last1=Global Burden of Disease Study 2013}}</ref>。聽力減退導致失能的人數約5%（3.6至5.38億），中度至重度失能的人數約1.24億<ref name="WHO2015" /><ref name="WHO2008">{{cite book|url=http://www.who.int/healthinfo/global_burden_disease/GBD_report_2004update_full.pdf|title=The global burden of disease: 2004 update|author=WHO|publisher=World Health Organization|year=2008|isbn=9789241563710|location=Geneva, Switzerland|pages=35|access-date=2017-08-26|archive-date=2013-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130624134606/http://www.who.int/healthinfo/global_burden_disease/GBD_report_2004update_full.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=The global burden of disabling hearing impairment: a call to action.|first1=BO|last2=Neumann|first2=KJ|date=1 May 2014|journal=Bulletin of the World Health Organization|issue=5|doi=10.2471/blt.13.128728|volume=92|pages=367–73|pmc=4007124|pmid=24839326|last3=Saunders|first3=JE|last1=Olusanya}}</ref>。中度至重度失能者中，有1.08億人（約87%）生活在中低收入國家<ref name="WHO2008" />。而有6500萬人於兒童時期就罹病<ref name="Peads2011">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FEf4EMjYSrgC&pg=PA602|title=Textbook of clinical pediatrics|last=Elzouki|first=Abdelaziz Y|date=2012|publisher=Springer|isbn=9783642022012|edition=2|location=Berlin|pages=602|access-date=2017-08-26|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107052444/https://books.google.com/books?id=FEf4EMjYSrgC&pg=PA602|dead-url=no}}</ref>。 使用手語和[[聾人文化|聾人文化]]成員的人認為自己和一般人有所差異而非疾病<ref name="NAD2014">{{cite web|url=http://nad.org/issues/american-sign-language/community-and-culture-faq|title=Community and Culture - Frequently Asked Questions|accessdate=31 July 2014|publisher=National Association of the Deaf|website=nad.org|archive-date=2015-12-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151227171131/http://nad.org/issues/american-sign-language/community-and-culture-faq|dead-url=no}}</ref>。大多數聾人文化成員反對治療耳聾<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pbs.org/wnet/soundandfury/cochlear/essay.html|title=Sound and Fury - Cochlear Implants - Essay|accessdate=2015-08-01|publisher=[[PBS|PBS]]|website=www.pbs.org|archive-date=2015-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706062633/http://www.pbs.org/wnet/soundandfury/cochlear/essay.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2013/08/understanding-deafness-not-everyone-wants-to-be-fixed/278527/|title=Understanding Deafness: Not Everyone Wants to Be 'Fixed'|accessdate=2015-08-01|publisher=''[[The_Atlantic|The Atlantic]]''|website=www.theatlantic.com|archive-date=2013-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130811070420/https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2013/08/understanding-deafness-not-everyone-wants-to-be-fixed/278527/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/9526045/Why-not-all-deaf-people-want-to-be-cured.html|title=Why not all deaf people want to be cured|accessdate=2015-08-02|publisher=''[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]''|website=www.telegraph.co.uk|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924153612/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/9526045/Why-not-all-deaf-people-want-to-be-cured.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，有一些人對耳蝸植入物有疑慮，認為可能會破壞他們的文化<ref name="Spa2005">{{cite journal|title=Defending Deaf Culture: The Case of Cochlear Implants|url=http://profiles.arts.monash.edu.au/rob-sparrow/download/Deaf-Culture.pdf|first1=Robert|date=2005|journal=The Journal of Political Philosophy|accessdate=30 November 2014|issue=2|volume=13|last1=Sparrow|archive-date=2014-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204170705/http://profiles.arts.monash.edu.au/rob-sparrow/download/Deaf-Culture.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 定義 ==
動物的聽覺靈敏度可以以其可以聽到的最小強度聲音來定義，也就是[[聽闕|聽闕]]。人和一些動物的聽闕可以用{{link-en|听力图|audiogram}}來表示。在量測時會用聽力計〈audiometer〉產生不同頻率的聲音，量測聲音在各頻率下可以使受測者有反應的最小強度。听力图也可用电生理测试（electro-physiological）的方式進行，受測者不需針對聲音進行反應。

動物的聽闕會隨著頻率不同而不同，若不同頻率、相同強度的聲音同時產生，有些頻率的聲音會相當大聲，而有些頻率的聲音卻會小到幾乎聽不見。一般而言，若提高聲音的[[振幅|振幅]]，聲音會比較容易被聽到，若動物使用聲音互相溝通，溝通所用聲音的頻率往往也是聽覺靈敏度最好的頻率。不同頻率下的聽覺靈敏度會受聽覺系統的各部份所影響，從外耳的生理特性到傳導訊號到大腦聽覺區的神經。
